The paper proposes a new optimization framework for large-scale non-convex sparsity-constrained problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization research. The paper also discusses the design of specific algorithms and presents experimental results on both synthetic and real-world datasets. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
